Sigma, Most of your line of sugestion pertaining to the control of the supply of guns and drugs looks to be the kind of thinking that is allready in use by the current policy. We know from the last 30 years in this country that these ideas are badly flawed and do not work. It's nothing but "feel good" ploitics. I believe that every law abiding American head of household should be required to own and maintain a firearm. Places in the world where this mentality exist have virtualy no violent crime at all. As well as several towns in America where this practice is a law. As far as criminals getting guns. It's gonna happen one way or the other. I'd rather have a fighting chance personally. Spoken like someone who has never touched an illegal drug in their life. I'm not advocating that you try illegal drugs mind you but it's a bit difficult to make a determination like that without the experience to back it up. I like my take on this better. It comes from real world experience, some personal and some second hand. They can never be effective for one simple reason. Only law abiding people obey the law. Criminals do not. There is an expression I've heard come from a great many not so law abiding people. "It's only illegal if you get caught." That's the criminal mentality. The laws you would put in place only serve to hurt the people who obey the laws. While out of desperation, greed and hatred the criminal element will take advantage of the laws by being willing to thwart them for personal gain where honest people will not. There are no easy answers to these issues. They have been with us for thousands of years. We do know however that what our country is doing is not working and we also know that as laws get tougher the crime gets worse. Laws are not the answer. Also one of the things I'm trying to get at: Heroin and other very hard and very dangerous drugs should not be in stores or anything like that. Society should also stop focusing on the drug. Eliminate heroin and someone will invent something more addictive and more dangerous. Focus on the Social problems that get people into doing heroin and work with that. It's not 100% effective but it's all you can do without causing nasty side effects. As far as lighter drugs... LSD, POT, X, Magic Mushrooms, and a few other relativly harmless drugs that are made out to be killers. These should be Legal, Sold and taxed. Amsterdam legalized Pot and saw a huge drop in the use of things like heroin and cocane. Also a huge drop in violent crime.
